SIMPLE: mightily
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mightily
<hw>Might"i*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Mighty</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a mighty manner; with might;
with great earnestness; vigorously; powerfully.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whereunto I also labor, striving according to his working, which
worketh in me <qex>mightily</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Col. i.
29.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To a great degree; very much.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Practical jokes amused us <qex>mightily</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mightiness</ent>⟦br⟧
